// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/lsp/fixtures/two_errors_same_position.nsl — fixture for
// `DiagnosticsSuite::SortOrder_SeverityOnTie` (T061). Exercises the
// `(line, character, severity)`-ascending sort tiebreaker per
// `diagnostic-mapping.contract.md` §6 / §7.5.
//
// The `function` keyword on line 1 emits two diagnostics at byte-
// identical `(line, character) = (1, 2)`:
//
//   * S26 warning at the `function` keyword begin (parser site,
//     `lib/Parse/ParseDecl.cpp` `parseFuncDefn`).
//   * S01 error at `FuncDefn.loc().begin()` (Sema site,
//     `lib/Sema/Constraints/S01_NoDoubleUnderscore.cpp` NK_FuncDefn
//     case) because the function name `bad__name` contains `__`.
//     `FuncDefn.loc()` begins at the `function` keyword (per
//     `parseFuncDefn`'s `rangeFromTo(kw.range().begin(), end_loc)`),
//     so the start position byte-matches the warning.
//
// The function name does NOT use a `_`-prefix because the lexer
// classifies `_`-prefix tokens via `classifyUnderscoreName` (N11)
// and any non-system-task spelling becomes `tk_unused_underscore`,
// which `consumeIdentifierLike` rejects — that would produce an
// `expected identifier` error at the *name*'s column instead of
// at the `function` kw column, breaking the position tie.
//
// LSP severity mapping (contract §2): Error → 1, Warning → 2. After
// the mapper's sort, the Error precedes the Warning at the same
// position. The fixture's filename retains the historical
// `two_errors_*` prefix paired with `two_errors_same_line.nsl`
// (T060); the actual diagnostics are one error + one warning.

module m {
  function bad__name { }
}
